<br>
I love this line (Scalia):<br>
<br>
“[T]he University of Michigan Law School’s mystical ‘critical mass’ justification for its discrimination by race challenges even the most gullible mind.”<br>
<br>
Here's part of Jeb Bush's statement:<br>
<br>
&quot;The Supreme Court's decision today acknowledges that race-conscious college admissions policies are ultimately at odds with the guarantee of equal protection under the law. Instead of striking down these policies on this basis, the court allowed their limited use, but suggested their eventual demise.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.visveres.myguilds.com/sigs/caledhon.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=radgen>Radgen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 774<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/23/03 3:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=747.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://radgen.homestead.com/files/Radgen5.jpg height=150 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> This was not a clear cut decisive decision.  Which is a shame.  The ideal of equal protection and the desirabilty of diversity are at odds and there needs to be clearly drawn lines.<br>
<br>
The Law school's system was upheld, the Undergrad system was shot down.  We are in exactly the same place we were before.<br>
<br>
The Court says race can be a factor, but has been maddenly vague about just HOW it can be used.  We now know what CAN'T be used, but this is going to come up again.  There will be another lawsuit and the court will again have to address this issue. <p><center><font face="lucida handwriting, arial" color="006800" size=+2><b>Radgen Waldjaeger</font></b><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="675f00" size=+1><b>Semi-retired Outrider of Karana</font><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="blue" size=+1>Shining Path</font></b><br><img src=http://radgen.homestead.com/files/tiger_run_md_clr.gif></center>
